56.4	Gurkha	Gurkha	Gurkha ( or ; also spelled Gorkha or Ghurka; Nepali: "Gorkhali" Nepali: ) is an ethnic community from Nepal. Their name derives from the Hindu warrior-saint Guru Gorakhnath (8th century ).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Gurkha_Soldier_Monument%2C_London_-_April_2008.jpg/220px-Gurkha_Soldier_Monument%2C_London_-_April_2008.jpg
